People like your mother,

259
00:16:58,166 --> 00:17:00,333
who sobbed and said she was
sorry for not noticing how much

260
00:17:00,416 --> 00:17:01,791
you were suffering.

261
00:17:01,875 --> 00:17:04,291
I spoke with Momoka as well,
who apologized profusely.

262
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:06,125
No way.

263
00:17:25,541 --> 00:17:27,500
Thank you both.

264
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:33,833
Too bad. We're all out of time.

265
00:17:33,916 --> 00:17:35,500
Goodbye.

266
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:38,958
[gasping] What the hell?

267
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:40,875
The invasion fleet
from Alpha Centauri

268
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:42,083
has finally come to Earth.

269
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:45,500
Humanity is finished
if nothing is done!

270
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:46,916
Well, then.

271
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,291
We'll have to resist the
invaders with our giant robot!

272
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:52,208
Your robot? Don't you mean
your space battleship?

273
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:53,583
Are you ready?

274
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:56,416
[gasps] Sure!

275
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:00,666
[KANZAKI]
Put them on the main monitor!

276
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,791
[HARUTO]
That fleet is huge!

277
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,666
Scramble fighter wing!

278
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,333
[NATSUKI, HARUTO]
Roger!

279
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:13,708
[KANZAKI] Pretty weak on
the cosplay front, Kanzaki.

280
00:18:22,666 --> 00:18:25,000
Unit One, engage!

281
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:30,041
Unit Two, engage!

282
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:32,416
[HARUTO]
Huh?

283
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,083
Have fun out there, you two!

284
00:18:34,166 --> 00:18:36,333
[gasps] Where'd she come from?

285
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:37,791
[ANNOUNCER 6A]
Emergency launch.

286
00:18:37,875 --> 00:18:40,916
To avoid danger, please
remain in your classrooms.

287
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,125
Repeat: Emergency Launch.

288
00:18:43,208 --> 00:18:46,750
To avoid danger, please remain
in your classrooms.

289
00:18:48,916 --> 00:18:52,125
Haruto, blasting off!

290
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:53,416
Go!

291
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,458
Natsuki, moving out!

292
00:19:06,958 --> 00:19:07,958
Time to link up!

293
00:19:08,041 --> 00:19:09,458
Roger!

294
00:19:26,125 --> 00:19:28,500
[laughs] This kicks ass!

295
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:30,416
Go, Giant Robot Natsuking!

296
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:31,416
What now?

297
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,958
Pretty cool name,
don't ya think?

298
00:19:33,041 --> 00:19:35,458
Yeah, not too bad, I guess.

299
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:38,125
Go! Natsuking!

300
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:52,541
We'll start off by kicking
things into gear!

301
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:53,375
You've got it!

302
00:19:53,458 --> 00:19:54,208
Here goes.

303
00:19:54,291 --> 00:19:57,083
[BOTH]
Natsuking kick!

304
00:19:57,166 --> 00:19:59,041
[yelling]

305
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:05,375
[HARUTO, NATSUKI]
Natsuking kick!

306
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,916
[panting]

307
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,500
There are too many.

308
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:19,666
Ready up, finishing move time!

309
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:20,750
I can't wait!

310
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:21,833
Here we go!

311
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:26,250
[BOTH]
Activate! Eye-Beam Laser Cannon!

312
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:43,750
You've got a nice smile.

313
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,750
What? Where'd that come from?

314
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:48,416
Who knew? You're quite
the <i>otaku,</i> aren't you?

315
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:51,000
You seemed to be having a pretty
good time yourself, old man.

316
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:54,875
Uh! What was that?
The cat's the old one!

317
00:20:55,458 --> 00:21:00,166
You know, it's been way too
long since I had any fun.

318
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:04,708
I wish I could have met someone
like you earlier, before I died.

319
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:07,291
Before you died? [gasps]

320
00:21:07,375 --> 00:21:09,333
This place isn't the afterlife.

321
00:21:09,416 --> 00:21:11,708
You've got Sleeping Beauty
Syndrome, Natsuki.

322
00:21:11,791 --> 00:21:15,916
Huh? "Sleeping Beauty
Syndrome"? What's that?

323
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,625
[HARUTO] It's the illness
that keeps people asleep.

324
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:22,083
Then, that means...
I must still be alive!

325
00:21:22,166 --> 00:21:24,333
[HARUTO]
Mm-hm.

326
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:27,500
Oh, good. That means
I can get out of here!

327
00:21:27,583 --> 00:21:30,291
That's all up to you,
from this point.

328
00:21:30,375 --> 00:21:33,041
Are you prepared to face
the harshness of reality?

329
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,625
That's a choice you'll have
to make for yourself.

330
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:37,791
I am ready.

331
00:21:39,958 --> 00:21:42,583
Thanks, Haruto.

332
00:21:42,666 --> 00:21:44,708
And farewell.

333
00:23:25,583 --> 00:23:28,083
[MIKU groans]
What do I do, Mei?

334
00:23:28,166 --> 00:23:30,208
I can't go to school
like this, can I?

335
00:23:30,291 --> 00:23:31,916
Uh! Don't ask me!

336
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,125
We're all getting flak
for picking on her!

337
00:23:34,208 --> 00:23:36,291
Just leave me alone!

338
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:39,666
[phone vibrates]

339
00:23:46,375 --> 00:23:48,583
[LILY] Imagine you were
a country's monarch.

340
00:23:48,666 --> 00:23:52,000
Think. What would you want
to protect, and why?

341
00:23:52,083 --> 00:23:54,000
[EGOS]
Think it over, baa!

342
00:23:54,083 --> 00:23:58,166
[LILY] Next time's dream is:
"And Now There Are None..."

